Two motorcyclists have died in what is believed to be a head-on collision along the R704 road outside Bloemfontein. JOHANNESBURG - Two motorcyclists have died in what is believed to be a head-on collision along the R704 road outside Bloemfontein in the Free State. Emergency services say they arrived on the scene to the motorbikes burning and declared the two men dead on the scene. ER24's Annine Dormehl says the road had to be closed for cleaning. ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene around 2pm and found both motorbike drivers burning. The road had to be closed for cleaning and local authorities were on the scene for further investigation. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)